<xref ref-type="table" rid="T4">4</xref>. Four risk factors, including GTV of radiation (&#x02265;5&#x000a0;cm<sup>3</sup> versus &#x0003c;5&#x000a0;cm<sup>3</sup>), postoperative T stage (stage I/II versus stage III/IV), locoregional recurrence of lymph node metastases (&#x02265;2 versus &#x0003c;1), and chemotherapy treatment (yes versus no) were characterized as significant independent prognostic factors. Patients who had small GTV, early postoperative T stage, small number of locoregional recurrent lymph node metastases, and chemotherapy treatment were likely to have a better prognosis.</p><table-wrap position="float" id="T4"><label>Table 4</label><caption><p>Multivariate analyses for prognostic factors in both groups</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups" border="1"><colgroup><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/></colgroup><thead valign="top"><tr><th align="left">&#x000a0;</th><th align="left"><bold>&#x003b2;</bold></th><th align="left"><bold>Sx</bold></th><th align="left"><bold>
